text: Oh Kyo-Moon (born March 2, 1972) is an archer from South Korea. He won a team silver medal and an individual bronze medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics. Oh also was a member of Korea's gold medal men's archery team at the 2000 Summer Olympics. In the men's individual competition he finished sixth. Oh was the world record holder for a single FITA with a score of 1379. That score was beaten by Oh Jin-Hyek at 2009 World Championship in Ulsan with 1386 points. ==References== ==Other websites== *Profile at databaseOlympmics.com Category:1972 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean archers Category:Olympic bronze medalists for South Korea Category:Olympic gold medalists for South Korea Category:Olympic silver medalists for South Korea Category:World record holders
